# .AGENTS — Agent Guidance for promptithesis

## Project Overview

`promptithesis` is a documentation-only repository. It collects and organizes
high-signal prompts for AI-assisted software development workflows. There is no
application source code, runtime, or build system.

## Repository Structure

```
promptithesis/
├── README.md          # Primary prompt collection and project overview
├── MANUAL_TESTS.md    # Detailed manual test cases for end-to-end verification
└── .AGENTS            # This file — guidance for AI agents working on the repo
```

## Goals

- Maintain a clean, well-organized collection of reusable prompts.
- Keep prompts generic enough to apply across many projects and languages.
- Group prompts into logical sections (Code Review, Architecture, Testing, etc.).
- Ensure all documentation is accurate, consistent, and up to date.

## Contribution Guidelines for Agents

1. **README.md** is the canonical source of truth for the prompt collection.
   When adding new prompts, follow the existing Markdown heading and blockquote
   format (`>` for the primary prompt, `> >` for the follow-up action prompt).
2. **MANUAL_TESTS.md** describes how a human or agent should manually verify
   the repository's content is correct and complete. Keep it updated whenever
   new sections are added to the README.
3. **Do not introduce source code, dependencies, or build artifacts** unless
   the project scope explicitly changes to include them.
4. All Markdown files should pass standard Markdown linting (consistent heading
   levels, blank lines around headings/lists/fences, etc.).

## Linting & Validation

There is no automated CI pipeline at this time. Manual validation steps are
described in `MANUAL_TESTS.md`.

If a linter is introduced in the future, add it here along with the command to
run it (e.g., `markdownlint **/*.md`).

## Versioning

This repository does not use semantic versioning. Track progress via Git
commits and PR descriptions.
